gurmukhi: ਜੈਸੇ ਫੂਲ ਫੂਲੇ ਤੇਤੇ ਫਲ ਨ ਲਾਗੈ ਦ੍ਰੁਮ ਲਾਗਤ ਜਿਤੇਕੁ ਪਰਪਕ ਨ ਸਕਲ ਹੈ
transliteration: Jaisay Dhool Dhoolay Taytay Dhal N Laagai Drouma , Laagat Jitayku Parapak N Sakal Hai ?
translation: All the flowers that blossom on a tree do not yield fruit. And whatever number of fruits appear, do not ripe to be eaten ultimately.

gurmukhi: ਜੇਤੇ ਸੁਤ ਜਨਮਤ ਜੀਅਤ ਨ ਰਹੈ ਨ ਤੇਤੇ ਜੀਅਤ ਹੈ ਜੇਤੇ ਤੇਤੇ ਕੁਲ ਨ ਕਮਲ ਹੈਂ
transliteration: Jaytay Sout Janamat Jeeat N Rahai N Taytay , Jeeat Hai Jaytay Taytay Kul N Kamal Hain ?
translation: All sons born do not survive to live but all those who live do not bring name and fame to their family.

gurmukhi: ਦਲ ਮਿਲ ਜਾਤ ਜੇਤੇ ਸੁਭਟ ਨ ਹੋੲਿ ਤੇਤੇ ਜੇਤਕ ਸੁਭਟ ਜੂਝ ਮਰਤ ਨ ਥਲ ਹੈਂ
transliteration: Dal Mil Jaat Jaytay Soubhat N Hoi Taytay , Jaytak Soubhat Joojh Marat N Dal Hain ?
translation: All those who join the army are not valiant soldiers. And those who are brave warriors do not die fighting in the battlefield.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਰਸੀ ਜੁਗਤਿ ਗੁਰ ਸਿਖ ਸਭ ਹੀ ਕਹਾਵੈ ਪਾਵਕ ਪ੍ਰਗਾਸ ਭੲੇ ਵਿਰਲੇ ਅਚੱਲ ਹੈਂ ||੩੬੮||
transliteration: Aarasee Jougati Gur Sikh Sabh Hee Kahaavai , Paavak Pragaas Bhaay Viralay Achal Hain ?368?
translation: A glass embedded in a finger ring cracks when brought near fire but a genuine stone is unaffected. Similarly like a genuine stone, everyone is known as a Sikh but a few emerge genuine when put through traits. (368)
